## III. System Architecture

### A. High-Level Architecture

VaidyaChain follows a **layered PWA architecture** with the following layers:

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│              Presentation Layer                 │
│   (index.html + styles.css – Responsive UI)     │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│           Application Logic Layer               │
│  app.js · auth.js · chatbot.js · i18n.js        │
│  search.js · notifications.js · exports.js      │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│         Blockchain Simulation Layer             │
│  blockchain-simulator.js · smart-contracts.js  │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│           Persistence Layer                     │
│  Firebase Firestore · localStorage (chain)      │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│         External Services Layer                 │
│  OpenRouter AI · Leaflet Maps · Chart.js        │
│  jsPDF · HTML5-QRCode · Firebase Auth           │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### B. Blockchain Data Model

Each block in the VaidyaChain blockchain contains:

```javascript
Block {
  timestamp: ISO8601 string,
  data: {
    type: 'collection' | 'lab-test' | 'manufacturing' | 
          'insurance-policy' | 'insurance-claim' |
          'dna-sequencing' | 'waste-collection' | ...,
    batchId: string,
    // type-specific fields
  },
  previousHash: SHA256 string,
  hash: SHA256 string
}
```

The chain maintains a `batchIndex` for O(1) batch lookup. Chain integrity is verified via the [isChainValid()](file:///c:/Users/phita/project10/vaidyachain/blockchain-simulator.js#67-82) method that recomputes all hashes and checks linkage.

### C. Smart Contract Architecture

Smart contracts are implemented as JavaScript objects with [execute(functionName, params, caller)](file:///c:/Users/phita/project10/vaidyachain/blockchain-simulator.js#147-159) semantics:

```javascript
SmartContract {
  contractName: string,
  code: Function,   // contract logic
  state: Object,    // persistent contract storage
  events: Array     // event log
}
```

Four contracts are deployed at initialization:
1. **paymentContract** – Escrow and automatic payment release upon quality gate clearance
2. **insuranceContract** – Parametric insurance with automated claim triggers
3. **qualityContract** – Quality threshold enforcement and batch approval automation
4. **reputationContract** – Stakeholder reputation scoring based on performance history

### D. Progressive Web App (PWA) Configuration

VaidyaChain is registered as a PWA via [manifest.json](file:///c:/Users/phita/project10/vaidyachain/manifest.json) and [sw.js](file:///c:/Users/phita/project10/vaidyachain/sw.js) (Service Worker), enabling:
- Offline functionality
- Home screen installation
- Background sync capability
- Mobile-first responsive design

