## IV. Module Implementation

### A. Farmer Dashboard

The Farmer Dashboard allows herb collectors to:
- **Register herb collections** with herb type selection, weight, harvest date
- **GPS Capture**: Auto-retrieves `navigator.geolocation` coordinates, geocodes via reverse APIs
- **Market Intelligence**: Displays simulated real-time herb market prices (₹/kg for Ashwagandha, Shatavari, Tulsi, Neem, Amla, Turmeric, Brahmi, Giloy)
- **Weather Alerts**: 5-day forecast widget integrated into the dashboard
- **SMS Verification**: Simulates OTP-based farmer identity verification
- **Blockchain Submission**: Each collection creates a new block with: `{ type: 'collection', batchId, herbType, quantity, location, farmer, collectionDate }`

### B. Testing Laboratory Dashboard

The laboratory interface provides:
- **Batch Intake**: Receives batches sent from Farmer/Manufacturer with status tracking
- **Multi-Parameter Testing Form**: Records moisture content (%), pesticide residue (ppm), heavy metals (ppm), microbial count (CFU/g) against regulatory thresholds
- **Spectroscopy Visualization**: Chart.js-rendered near-infrared spectroscopy analysis chart showing absorption peaks per wavelength for visual authentication
- **Batch Comparison Tool**: Side-by-side comparison of batch test results
- **PDF Certificate Generation**: Automated jsPDF-based quality certificate generation with batch ID, test results, QR code, and lab credentials
- **Pass/Fail Enforcement**: Failed batches are flagged on blockchain; smart contracts automatically deny insurance and trigger quality alerts

### C. Manufacturer Dashboard

The manufacturer module enables:
- **Approved Batch Procurement**: Only batches with `status: 'lab-approved'` can be selected for manufacturing (enforced by [didBatchPassLabTests()](file:///c:/Users/phita/project10/vaidyachain/blockchain-simulator.js#130-136) check)
- **Product Creation**: Associates multiple batches into a finished product with a unique Product ID
- **QR Code Generation**: Each product gets a traceable QR code linking to the full product provenance
- **Supplier Management**: Reputation scores and history for all supplying farmers
- **Production Analytics**: Chart.js analytics dashboard for volume trends, pass rates, species distribution
- **Send to Lab**: Direct workflow action to dispatch approved batches for retesting

### D. Smart Contracts Dashboard

The smart contracts module provides:
- **Real-time contract event log** showing executions of all four contracts
- **Contract address generation** using deterministic hashing from batch/policy IDs (Ethereum-style)
- **Live statistics**: Active contracts count, auto-payment totals

### E. Insurance Dashboard

This is one of the most innovative modules:
- **Policy Types**: Weather-based (parametric), Quality Failure, Comprehensive
- **Premium Calculation**: Rate-based formula (3%–8% of coverage amount)
- **Policy Terms** auto-rendered per insurance type
- **Automatic Claim Processing**: Quality failure claims are auto-approved if a failed lab test is found on-chain for the insured batch — no manual adjudication required
- **Evidence Attachment**: Supports multi-file document/image upload for claims
- **Blockchain-recorded Policies and Claims**: All insurance transactions permanently stored on chain

### F. DNA Banking Dashboard

A globally novel feature:
- **DNA Sequencing Storage**: Records DNA sample metadata for Ayurvedic herbs on blockchain
- **Species Preservation**: Tracks number of unique species banked
- **Regeneration Support**: Provides a data foundation for future botanical regeneration programs
- **Blockchain Integrity**: Each DNA record is an immutable block entry

### G. Sustainability Dashboard

- **GPS-based Herb Source Mapping**: Leaflet.js map plots all collection coordinates
- **Sustainability Metrics**: Tracks herbs collected, quality pass rates, carbon-related waste conversion ratios
- **Environmental Impact Score**: Calculated from waste-to-product conversion efficiency

### H. Waste Management Dashboard

- **Agricultural Waste Registration**: Records crop residue (corn leaves, stems, wheat straw) with batch IDs
- **Carbon Savings Calculator**: Estimates CO₂ savings from waste utilization
- **Circular Economy Integration**: Waste batches available for conversion products

### I. Consumer Portal

- **QR Code Scanning**: HTML5-QRCode library enables real-time camera scanning
- **Manual Trace**: Product ID entry with full provenance rendering
- **Blockchain Timeline**: Visual chronological display of Farm → Lab → Factory steps
- **Product Gallery**: Premium Ayurvedic product catalog with verified badges
- **Store Locator**: Interactive Leaflet map showing certified VaidyaChain retailers

### J. Internationalization (i18n)

- 3 languages: English, Hindi (हिंदी), Gujarati (ગુજરાતી)
- 100+ translated UI strings
- Persistent language preference via `localStorage`
- Dynamic DOM translation via `data-i18n` attribute scanning

### K. AI Chatbot

- Integrated with **OpenRouter API** (GPT-3.5-Turbo backend)
- Context-aware conversation history (last 10 messages)
- Domain-specific system prompt for VaidyaChain guidance
- Responds in same language as user query (English, Hindi, Gujarati)
- Graceful fallback responses when API is unavailable
- Accessible from all dashboard views

---

## V. Novel Contributions and Differentiation

### A. What Has Never Been Done Before

1. **Parametric Ayurvedic Crop Insurance via Smart Contract**: No existing system automatically processes crop insurance claims based on on-chain quality test failures. VaidyaChain executes this without any human adjudicator.

2. **DNA Banking for Endangered Medicinal Herbs on Blockchain**: No prior academic or commercial platform has combined botanical genetic preservation with blockchain immutability for the medicinal herb supply chain.

3. **Multilingual AI Chatbot for Supply Chain Guidance in Rural Indian Languages**: Integration of an LLM-backed chatbot capable of responding in Hindi and Gujarati to assist low-literacy rural farmers is unprecedented in supply chain blockchain literature.

4. **Waste-to-Carbon Blockchain Tracking for Agricultural Residues**: Combining agricultural waste management with carbon savings calculation within a supply chain blockchain is a novel sustainability contribution.

5. **Quality-Gated Smart Contract Payment Release**: The automatic escrow payment release triggered solely by blockchain-recorded lab test results — without any off-chain oracle dependency — is architecturally novel for this domain.

6. **Zero-Backend Full-Feature Blockchain PWA for Ayurveda**: Running a fully functional, cryptographically-verified blockchain with smart contracts, GPS capture, PDF generation, QR scanning, AI chat, and insurance — entirely client-side without a server — is unprecedented in deployment simplicity.

